**How to make a Lemon Fiesta Cake**
   First, preheat the oven to 325 degrees F. Then, grease and flour a Bundt pan.
Second, add 1/2 cup cream, 2 tablespoons butter and 1 1/2 cups sugar until it becomes fluffy. Remember to add eggs one at a time beating after each addition. Next, blend in the lemon peel. Third, take a separate bowl and mix flour, salt, soda and baking powder in it. After that, add flour mixture alternately with buttermilk to creamed butter mixture. Then, add lemon extract and raisins. Finally, you can bake it at 325 degrees F for 50 minutes and cool it 5 minutes. After finish baking it, turn it out onto a serving plate. Then, prick hot cake with skewer or fork and pour on lemon topping. At last, combine 1/3 cup sugar, 1/3 cup butter and water in a saucepan and heat until butter melts. Then, add lemon juice and spoon over your hot cake. Now, you can enjoy a light, lemony, fluffy, and festive lemon-accented cake with raisins.

