**How To Make An Aromatherapy Candle With Essential Oils**
   Essential oils can play a great role in helping you unwind at the end of a hard day, adding freshness to the air and creating an energizing mood. Here’s how to make an aromatherapy candle with essential oils. First, measure out 1 cup of Wilderness Family Naturals Craft Oil every candle you wish to make. Second, over a double boiler, gently warm the oil until it is liquefied, but not hot. A glass bowl fitted atop a pot of boiling water works as a double boiler. Alternatively, you can heat the coconut craft oil in a slow (200-degrees Fahrenheit) oven or even in bowl set in a Crock Pot on the lowest temperature setting. Next, add 1/4 cup of beeswax pastilles per 1 cup of melted craft oil and gently melt, stirring frequently. Please be careful at this stage; oil spilled on an open flame such as a gas stove can cause a fire. Third, add wicks to the jars. Take part of the wick and wrap it around a pencil and place in the middle of the jar with the wick hanging down. This will keep the wick in place while the oil and wax completely cool. After that, pour the scented oil into the prepared jar. Allow the candle to cool completely, then trim the wick so that it is about 1-inch long. After the wax and oil are all melted together, allow the mixture to cool slightly. Finally, as it is cooling, add 25 drops of essential oils. At last, to use your aromatherapy candle with essential oils, simply place it in an open area away from anything flammable. Burn it for at least half an hour each time.


