**My favorite natural attraction in Taipei**
In Taipei, Yangmingshan National Park is my favorite natural place to escape away from the hustle and bustle of the city. First, it is easily accessible from downtown. Second, because of affluent sulfur buried under the mountains, you can enjoy a relaxing soak in a steaming, silky-smooth hot spring with the fresh breeze and grand view of mountains. Third, the beautiful scene of Yangmingshan in different seasons can always amaze you. For example, in spring, Yangmingshan brings numerous fragrant flowers, painting the hills a shade of red. And, autumn is the best time to see the tasseled silvergrass in full bloom, glittering in the sunlight as a golden sea. In short, if you feel overwhelmed by the crowded Taipei City, Yamgminshan National Park is the best place to experience a scenic retreat for your mind, body, and soul.

