**Should I replace longhand notes with laptops?**
In my opinion, the way people take notes should depend on situations, so I disagree that we should ban students using laptops for note-taking in class. In some lectures, it is important to take notes more precisely, even word by word to get the quotes; at that time, it would be wiser to choose a laptop than pen and paper. But, if you want a deeper understanding of the content or want to grab the core thing faster, I agree that you should take notes by hand. Based on my own experience, when I take notes by hand, I obviously can’t write down every single word. Hence, I need to quickly summarize and find the key points while I listen; and this process stimulates my brain to organize the content quickly. On the contrary, while I use my laptop to take notes, due to the fact that it is too easy to type down every information, I won’t spend much time on digesting the contents but spend more time on typing more notes. What’s worse, after I go home, I seldom look at the notes on my laptop because it contains too many details, which make me feel tired to organize them. It seems that if I take notes by my laptop in class, I am more likely to lose the first chance of organizing contents and forming strong memory in class. Finally, I would say that people should be more aware of what they choose to take notes according to different needs.



